tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE fingerprint_images (
  image_id INT,
  image_data BYTEA,
  capture_time TIMESTAMP,
  user_id INT,
  PRIMARY KEY (image_id)
);

CREATE TABLE FingerprintImages (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  fingerprint_data BYTEA
)

CREATE TABLE Users (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50),
  password_hash VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE Identification (
  identification_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  fingerprint_id INT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES Users(user_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (fingerprint_id) REFERENCES FingerprintImages(id)
)

CREATE TABLE FingerprintImages (
  fingerprint_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  image BYTEA
)

CREATE TABLE Users (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50),
  password VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE UserFingerprints (
  user_id INT,
  fingerprint_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES Users(user_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (fingerprint_id) REFERENCES FingerprintImages(fingerprint_id)
)

CREATE TABLE AccessLogs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  access_time TIMESTAMP,
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES Users(user_id)
)

CREATE TABLE MatchingResults (
  match_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  fingerprint_id INT,
  user_id INT,
  match_score FLOAT,
  FOREIGN KEY (fingerprint_id) REFERENCES FingerprintImages(fingerprint_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES Users(user_id)
)
